(24. Freeze / pointer / handoff concept) Tj
T*
(--------------------------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A freeze is an accepted state.) Tj
T*
(A pointer records the identity of that state.) Tj
T*
(A handoff package preserves the route back to that state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A pointer should include:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- SHA256 values) Tj
T*
(- Git commit) Tj
T*
(- branch) Tj
T*
(- remote) Tj
T*
(- boundary status) Tj
T*
(- handoff ZIP, if present) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If app.py SHA changes, it is a new app state.) Tj
T*
(If Manual PDF SHA changes, it is a new documentation distribution state.) Tj
